Question :- 6

Walk through the asynchronous sequence of the delete operation: how you call the
database method, how you update the widget's state, and how you handle the scenario where
the database throws an exception midway through the operation.

Ans :- 

When the user taps the Cancel Order button, the app starts an asynchronous delete operation.
Because deleting data from a SQLite database can take some time,
the app does not freeze while waiting.Instead, it continues to respond to the user.
The app calls the database's delete method and waits for it to finish using await. 
Once the database confirms that the order has been deleted successfully, 
the app updates its local order list and calls setState(). Calling setState() tells Flutter that the data has changed,
so it rebuilds the widget and the deleted order disappears from the screen immediately.
